.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-4-8::.
The people use 4 different means of transport: train, snowmobile, van, jet-ski
There are 4 different nationalities: italian, spanish, australian, polish
City: new-york, miami, boston, london
1. the person traveling to london is on the left or right of the person traveling to boston##3
2. the australian is the person driving the train##1
3. the polish is the person driving the van##1
4. the person driving the van is on the right of the person traveling to boston##1
5. the person traveling to miami is between the italian and the person driving the train##2
6. the person traveling to london is on the left or right of the australian##3
7. the person driving the train is in an even position##4
8. the person driving the train is between the person driving the snowmobile and the person driving the van##2

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |     2      |       3       |     4      |
| Transport         | snowmobile | train      | van       | jet-ski    |
| Nationality           | spanish  | australian  | polish | italian |
| City   | london      | boston | miami         | new-york    |

